class Solution {
    public int minFlipsMonoIncr(String s) {
        int ones = 0, flips = 0;
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (c == '1') ones++;
            else flips = Math.min(flips + 1, ones);
        }
        return flips;
    }
}
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution iterates through the string once, keeping track of the number of ones encountered so far and the minimum number of flips required to make the string monotone increasing. It achieves high efficiency by minimizing the number of operations and using a single pass through the string.

